            <!--[if gt IE 8]><!--></noscript><!--[endif]-->
</div>
</div>
<h4 class="flush--third--bottom font-size--h6 clear-left">Source: Office for National Statistics – Consumer price inflation</h4>
<div id="notes-0a502675" class="notes-holder-js">
<h5 class="flush--third--bottom js-notes-title font-size--16 padding-top--0">Notes:</h5>
<ol>
<li>Individual contributions may not sum to the total because of rounding.</li>
<li>More information on the contents of each group can be found in Table 3 in the accompanying <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230216220653/https://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/inflationandpriceindices/datasets/consumerpriceinflation">Consumer price inflation dataset</a>.</li>
<li>CPIH is the Consumer Prices Index including owner occupiers’ housing costs.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h4 class="print--hide padding-top--0 margin-top--0 font-size--h6 clear-left"><span role="text">Download this chart <span class="visuallyhidden">Figure 6: Contributions to the CPIH annual rate from 3 of the 12 divisions largest since start of National Statistics series in 2006</span></span></h4>
<a class="btn btn--primary print--hide js-chart-image-src" data-filename="0a502675" href="/web/20230216220653/https://www.ons.gov.uk/chartimage?uri=/economy/inflationandpriceindices/bulletins/consumerpriceinflation/january2023/0a502675" download="Figure 6: Contributions to the CPIH annual rate from 3 of the 12 divisions largest since start of National Statistics series in 2006" data-gtm-title="Figure 6: Contributions to the CPIH annual rate from 3 of the 12 divisions largest since start of National Statistics series in 2006" data-gtm-type="download-chart-image" aria-label="Download Figure 6: Contributions to the CPIH annual rate from 3 of the 12 divisions largest since start of National Statistics series in 2006 as an image">Image</a>
